videoTitle: New study finds rare side effects from COVID-19 vaccine 💉 #Health #Vaccines #COVID19

comments.author: @Legal_Sweetie333
comments.text: Swelling in the brain is a lot worse than 2 weeks of a bad cold
comments.comment-summary: "The commenter is noting the severity of brain swelling compared to enduring two weeks of a severe cold."

replies.author: @MagpieMalone
replies.text: At least it isn't contagious right? 🤔

replies.author: @Monakhalidi0513
replies.text: I got Johnson and Johnson I've always been fairly thin I've never been overweight I'm 5-0 probably right around $100 105 lb. I got the Johnson & Johnson vaccine in May of 2021 as soon as they were available in my state I got it on May 4th when I could get an appointment and it was available May 1st I got it and I started gaining weight I couldn't understand why I was exercising and went to my doctor and they said everything was fine and might just be because of the shutdown I said to shut down is over the vaccines out I still have trouble keeping the weight off I have gained 805 lbs from getting that vaccine I haven't changed anything that I've been eating I've had my thyroid checked I've had everything done test after test and that is the only thing then I have done differently is getting the vaccine and it was right around June 2021 that I noticed I needed to get a shirt that was a little bit bigger and it's just been going up from there. I have tried everything to get the weight off and I just can't and the doctors have no idea why I'm gaining weight for a couple other people say that they got Johnson and Johnson and they've gained weight

replies.author: @macantakai
replies.text: The more times you get covid the more likely you are to get long covid and/or organ damage.  Not all viruses are the same.
